00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:38.288
That's how simple it is.

00:01:38.288 --> 00:01:41.191
OK, this is the principle behind it

00:01:41.191 --> 00:01:45.928
where a is the coefficient.

00:01:45.928 --> 00:01:47.701
Let's move on.

00:01:50.535 --> 00:01:54.712
OK, now what we're going to do is the base method.

00:01:54.712 --> 00:01:57.586
OK, this is used to multiply numbers

00:01:57.586 --> 00:01:59.671
very close to the powers of 10,

00:01:59.671 --> 00:02:02.554
like 10, 100, 1,000, and so on.

00:02:02.554 --> 00:02:06.491
So we have a sum here, say 99 times 97.

00:02:06.491 --> 00:02:12.098
OK, now tell me, is 99 more than 100 or less than 100?

00:02:12.098 --> 00:02:14.231
Less by how much?

00:02:14.231 --> 00:02:18.377
So we write minus 01.

00:02:18.377 --> 00:02:22.059
And 97 is less than 100 by how much?

00:02:22.059 --> 00:02:23.862
So we write minus 03.

00:02:23.862 --> 00:02:25.613
So what we're going to do is

00:02:25.613 --> 00:02:27.265
we're going to cross subtract

00:02:27.265 --> 00:02:31.026
and get the first part of the answer, like this.

00:02:31.026 --> 00:02:32.934
We're going to do cross subtraction.

00:02:32.934 --> 00:02:36.819
97 minus 01 would give us

00:02:36.819 --> 00:02:37.834
96.

00:02:37.834 --> 00:02:42.233
and we multiply 03 times 01 vertically,

00:02:42.233 --> 00:02:46.382
and we get an answer of 03.

00:02:46.382 --> 00:02:47.522
Let's check another sum.

00:02:47.522 --> 00:02:49.891
Try and do it yourselves.

00:02:49.891 --> 00:02:54.056
We got 98, which is,

00:02:54.056 --> 00:02:56.526
is it more than a 100, less than 100?

00:02:56.526 --> 00:02:57.843
By how much?

00:02:57.843 --> 00:03:00.295
And 97 is 3.

00:03:00.295 --> 00:03:01.677
So we got 98,

00:03:01.677 --> 00:03:03.094
we go crosswise,

00:03:03.094 --> 00:03:04.999
we got 98 minus 3,

00:03:04.999 --> 00:03:06.699
or we can do 97 minus 2,

00:03:06.699 --> 00:03:09.103
they'll all give you the same answer.

00:03:09.103 --> 00:03:12.108
So that would give us 95.

00:03:12.108 --> 00:03:14.557
And the second part would be

00:03:14.557 --> 00:03:16.103
06.

00:03:16.103 --> 00:03:18.403
So that's our answer.

00:03:20.650 --> 00:03:23.016
OK, let's take a bigger number.

00:03:23.016 --> 00:03:24.183
Let's try this one.

00:03:24.183 --> 00:03:27.094
Here the base is 1,000.

00:03:27.094 --> 00:03:31.001
So we got -004,

00:03:31.001 --> 00:03:33.828
